VM's in Azure are modeled similarly to Hyper-V
  Use VHD's
  Virtual Network's

VM's are billed by tier
  the higher the tier the more cpu/ram/storage .. and the more cost

Can create vms from templates

To capture a Windows VM in the Resource Manager model, you will use Azure PowerShell, the Azure
CLI, or the Azure Resource Explorer tool. Capturing a VM is not yet possible in the Azure portal.

VM's can Scale
